T1  - Bias and Variance Approximation in Value Function Estimates
AU  - Mannor, Shie
AU  - Simester, Duncan
AU  - Sun, Peng
AU  - Tsitsiklis, John N.
Y1  - 2007/02/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0614
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1060.0614
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 308
EP  - 322
VL  - 53
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We consider a finite-state, finite-action, infinite-horizon, discounted reward Markov decision process and study the bias and variance in the value function estimates that result from empirical estimates of the model parameters. We provide closed-form approximations for the bias and variance, which can then be used to derive confidence intervals around the value function estimates. We illustrate and validate our findings using a large database describing the transaction and mailing histories for customers of a mail-order catalog firm.
AB  - We consider a finite-state, finite-action, infinite-horizon, discounted reward Markov decision process and study the bias and variance in the value function estimates that result from empirical estimates of the model parameters. We provide closed-form approximations for the bias and variance, which can then be used to derive confidence intervals around the value function estimates. We illustrate and validate our findings using a large database describing the transaction and mailing histories for customers of a mail-order catalog firm.
